  "text": "It is well known that improvements in the timing of initial antibiotic administration, appropriate choice of antibiotic agents, and short durations of antibiotic administration are inversely related to the risk of SSI [CITATION_1] . Therefore, there is an urgent need to organize the infection control measures for UTI and pneumonia. Specific guidelines for these infections, which are crucial at the national level and P: probability value according to multivariate logistic regression analysis (NS: not significant; P ≤ 0.05; P ≤ 0.01; P ≤ 0.001); † underwent previous surgical procedure (in the 30 days before onset of infection or the 30 days before the survey day).",
